<p itemprop="description">Software design involves creating the structure, components, and interfaces of software systems to meet functional and non-functional requirements while ensuring maintainability and scalability.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand software design principles and recognise the importance of good design in creating maintainable and scalable government software systems.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can contribute to software design activities, apply basic design patterns, and create simple software designs following established standards and guidelines.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can design complex software systems, apply advanced design patterns, and establish design standards and practices for development teams.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can lead software design strategy, establish design frameworks and methodologies, and mentor others in advanced software design techniques.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

